This paper discusses the susceptibility of neural networks to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper explores the implications of theoretical guarantees for real-world problems, which is also relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
